        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down Farnborough Kent</placeName>
                    <date>Dec. 18<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>.</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
<p>I am much obliged for your note &amp; for your remittance of <hi rend="superscript">£</hi>188 . <hi rend="superscript">s</hi> 15 . <hi rend="superscript">d</hi> 2. to my account.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> I am <hi rend="underline">very</hi> glad to hear that agricultural affairs are improving a little. With respect to Rent, I feel sure you will do what is right.</p>
<p>Believe me | My dear Sir | Yours sincerely | C. Darwin <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/> J. Higgins Es<hi rend="superscript">q</hi></p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">CD recorded the receipt of the sum of £189 10<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 2<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. in his Classed account book (Down House MS) on 8 January 1853. His Account book indicates that he gave John Higgins the sum of 15<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. on 19 December 1852.</note>
        </div>        
            
